author: butek
msg: Internationalize tcpmon.  The difference between this and the rest of AXIS is:
1.  tcpmon has its own tcpmon.properties file.
2.  tcpmon has its own getMessages method which never fails; it takes a default
string, and if the lookup of the message key fails, the default string is returned.

author: gdaniels
msg: If we're creating a handler based on a reference type (rather than a
direct java class), don't write the options, because they will assumedly
have already have been set by the original definition we're referencing.
Add a unit test for handler options, which tests option retrieval for both
the direct and the reference case.
